{"info": {"author": "Belousow Makc", "author_email": "lib.bmw@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries"], "description": "=======\nConflow\n=======\n\n.. image:: https://travis-ci.org/singulared/conflow.svg?branch=master\n    :target: https://travis-ci.org/singulared/conflow\n.. image:: https://codecov.io/gh/singulared/conflow/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\n  :target: https://codecov.io/gh/singulared/conflow\n\nProject in early beta. Work in progress!\n\nConflow organizes layered configurations for Python applications.\nConflow allows you to use default settings and extend or override it\nvia merging settings from different sources:\n- Python dictionaries\n- Files: yaml, json, ini\n- Environment variables\n\nQuickstart\n==========\n\n.. code-block:: bash\n\n  pip install conflow\n\nUsage\n=====\n\n.. code-block:: python\n\n  import os\n  from conflow import Config, from_env\n\n  DEFAULT_SETTINGS = {\n      'db': {\n          'master': {\n              'host': 'localhost',\n              'port': 5432,\n          },\n          'slave': {\n              'host': 'localhost',\n              'port': 5433,\n          }\n      }\n  }\n\n  config = Config().merge(DEFAULT_SETTINGS)\n  assert config.db.master.host() == 'localhost'\n\n  os.environ['APP_DB__MASTER__HOST'] = 'remote_host'\n  env_settings = from_env('APP')\n\n  config = Config().merge(DEFAULT_SETTINGS).merge(env_settings)\n  assert config.db.master.host() == 'remote_host'\n\nMotivation\n==========\nIf you are tired of making local, test, stage and production profiles in each project, then Conflow is for you.\nConflow allows you to fetch and merge configs from different places - yaml files, environment variables etc.\n", "description_content_type": "text/x-rst", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/singulared/conflow", "keywords": "development,configuration,management", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "Belousow Makc", "maintainer_email": "lib.bmw@gmail.com", "name": "conflow", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/conflow/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/conflow/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/singulared/conflow", "Repository": "https://github.com/singulared/conflow"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/conflow/0.0.2/", "requires_dist": ["PyYAML (>=5.1,<6.0)", "typing_extensions (>=3.7,<4.0)"], "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "summary": "Python configuration manager.", "version": "0.0.2", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/singulared/conflow\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"https://travis-ci.org/singulared/conflow.svg?branch=master\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/e5d8e2cfc209395cefff1dbff9fe60f0e6ce54cb/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f73696e67756c617265642f636f6e666c6f772e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://codecov.io/gh/singulared/conflow\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"https://codecov.io/gh/singulared/conflow/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/a48a9d2cc242027a047a8276f4d9294912fd6015/68747470733a2f2f636f6465636f762e696f2f67682f73696e67756c617265642f636f6e666c6f772f6272616e63682f6d61737465722f67726170682f62616467652e737667\"></a>\n<p>Project in early beta. Work in progress!</p>\n<p>Conflow organizes layered configurations for Python applications.\nConflow allows you to use default settings and extend or override it\nvia merging settings from different sources:\n- Python dictionaries\n- Files: yaml, json, ini\n- Environment variables</p>\n<div id=\"quickstart\">\n<h2>Quickstart</h2>\n<pre>pip install conflow\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div id=\"usage\">\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">os</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">conflow</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Config</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">from_env</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">DEFAULT_SETTINGS</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'db'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"s1\">'master'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"s1\">'host'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'localhost'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"s1\">'port'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">5432</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">},</span>\n        <span class=\"s1\">'slave'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"s1\">'host'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'localhost'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"s1\">'port'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">5433</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">config</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Config</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">merge</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">DEFAULT_SETTINGS</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">db</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">master</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">host</span><span class=\"p\">()</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s1\">'localhost'</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">os</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">environ</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s1\">'APP_DB__MASTER__HOST'</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'remote_host'</span>\n<span class=\"n\">env_settings</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">from_env</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'APP'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">config</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Config</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">merge</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">DEFAULT_SETTINGS</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">merge</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">env_settings</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">db</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">master</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">host</span><span class=\"p\">()</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s1\">'remote_host'</span>\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div id=\"motivation\">\n<h2>Motivation</h2>\n<p>If you are tired of making local, test, stage and production profiles in each project, then Conflow is for you.\nConflow allows you to fetch and merge configs from different places - yaml files, environment variables etc.</p>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6528506, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "cde04106ca39175dd1b8877d8b5bc639", "sha256": "095b97120ae68384bc4984a6d73bd08aee42362e17d3e24c67cba6300a15aea4"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "conflow-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "cde04106ca39175dd1b8877d8b5bc639", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "size": 9583, "upload_time": "2020-01-27T19:57:03", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-01-27T19:57:03.791991Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhost